info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued April 23 at 8:25AM CDT until April 28 at 7:00PM CDT by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...FLOOD WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 1130 AM CDT THIS MORNING... * WHAT...Flooding caused by rain and snowmelt is expected. * WHERE...Portions of north central Minnesota and northeast Minnesota, including the following counties, in north central Minnesota, Itasca and Koochiching. In northeast Minnesota, St. Louis. * WHEN...Until 1130 AM CDT. * IMPACTS...Flooding of rivers, creeks, streams, and other low-lying and flood-prone locations is imminent or occurring. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 825 AM CDT, Rain and snowmelt is occurring, and will cause flooding. Between 3 and 4 inches of rain have fallen. - More rain from thunderstorms will occur this morning. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... International Falls, Ely, Lake Vermilion, Birchdale, Littlefork, Cook, Marcell, Bigfork, Nett Lake, Orr, Big Falls, Meadow Brook, Northome, Winton, Ash Lake, Kabetogama, Effie, Squaw Lake, Crane Lake and Mizpah. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.
